//Sailors for Granted//
Sunda Kelapa Port. It‚Äôs an old port located on the estuarine of Ciliwung River. Decades ago, it used to play a major part in the development of Jakarta but since the creation of Port of Tanjung Priok in 1992, Sunda Kelapa Port plays a lesser and lesser significant role in Indonesia‚Äôs trans-shipment cargo traffic. And nowadays, only accommodates a few local inter-island freight shipment that still uses pinisi, a traditional two-masted wooden sailing ship. But beyond that, it holds a story about the locals.
.
